<body class="slides zoom horizontal noPreload animated ">

  <section class="slide fade-1 kenBurns slideWhite blue" data-name="intro" data-title="Intro">
    <div class="content">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="wrap">

          <div class="fix-12-12 left">
            <ul class="flex reverse verticalCenter">
              <li class="col-12-12 left toRight section-header">
                <h5 class=" ae-2 fromLeft subtitle underline">in this section</h5>
                <ul class="grid">
                  <li class="col-7-12 left ae-4 fromAbove toLeft align-left ">
                    <h1 class=" margin-bottom-2 ae-2 fromLeft">[Does my syllabus demonstrate equity for racially/ethnically minoritized students?]</h1>
                    <br/>
                    <h3 class="margin-bottom-2 ae-2 fromLeft text-yellow ">
                      <i class="far fa-clock margin-right-1"></i>  10 min exercise
                    </h3>
                    <br/>
                    <%= link_to "Let's Explore", s3_1_path, class: "button cueRed gradient ae-3 circle"%>
                  </li>
                  <li class="col-5-12 ae-4 fromAbove ">
                      <h4 class=" ae-2 fromLeft text-yellow">Outcomes</h4>
                    <p class="ae-3 left">
                       A greater understanding of the intentional (or unintentional) messages your syllabus communicates, particularly to students from minoritized racial/ethnic groups, and (potentially) new equity-minded practices you can experiment with and incorporate into your syllabi.
                    </p>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="background" style="background-image:url(https://www.sccpre.cat/mypng/full/145-1456885_moderate-red-curve-gradient-graphics-background-graphic.png);"></div>

